social_posts.post_text:
Ahhh, #TheParisApartment is into the final round of the @goodreads Choice Awards! This is thanks to you and your very generous votes, wonderful readers… THANK YOU! 

Voting for the final round is open until December 4th — so you can head there now if you want to vote for your favourite reads in all categories. Link in bio ✨

Absolutely over the moon about this — second place in the @goodreads awards for Mystery & Thriller, sandwiched between the magnificent winner, The Maid by @nitaprose, and the most excellent @misterosman. THANK YOU so much if you voted and I’m so grateful that you took the time … you have made my week! ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️

Memories of a very festive signing trip all round Scotland, not sure we quite walked 500 miles but it felt like it! Thank you lovely welcoming Scottish booksellers with your beautiful bookshops and sustaining shortbread! We had a blast.

Book baby incoming / real baby incoming 😳🔜

(Trying to find something to wear besides my husband’s shirts and some increasingly tight dungarees)

First ever event in the US, in conversation with fabulous @andibartz! Monday 27th Feb in Brooklyn, NY at St Joseph’s University — partnering with the the brilliant @greenlightbklyn. Come join us! Link for tickets in bio.

@emilyhenrywrites — I am so sorry about the state of this #HappyPlace ARC but it’s a sign of how much it has been loved! Thank you for this glorious read that has accompanied me on all my US travels … I have fallen head over heels for Harriet, Wyn and their gang and I’m actually pretty devastated my journey with them is over 💔💔💔. Thank you!!!
Signing copies yesterday at New York must-visit @themysteriousbookshop — a joy and honour to meet the legendary Otto Penzler and his brilliant team!
Four weeks on the @nytimes bestseller list for #TheParisApartment paperback! Thank you so much if you’ve bought a copy! ❤️

INSTAGRAM LIVE coming next week! Excited to talk to @thestigabell about his masterful debut crime novel Death Under A Little Sky on April 12th. Tune in if you’re looking for your next great read or just fancy hearing us chat about our favourite thrillers, heroes of the genre and top tips for writing crime…

Today’s the last day to vote for the @harrogatefestivals @theakstonbrewery Crime Awards shortlist I am in some fabulous/ intimidating company on this long list and would be SUPER grateful for your vote if you enjoyed The Paris Apartment! Link in bio…

Summer cuddles in my favourite cafe @juniper_arundel (most of the next book was written here) ✨

📸 @sue_the_well_house_gardener
Wandering the backstreets of Bonifacio, Corsica — I was first enchanted by this place aged ten and it was a key location in my first book, The Book of Lost & Found!
Tomorrow @piccadillywaterstones I have the very great honour of interviewing the multi-talented @richardcarmitage about his brilliant debut novel #Geneva — come join us!
Not saying I have a fave, but the Japanese edition of The Guest List (which I’ve just received) is pretty special! ✨
Happy nearly new year friends! I’ve been finishing the year with a final push on #TheMidnightFeast… coming to a bookshelf near you in 2024! I’ve had such (evil) fun with this one 👀🍴
